claim.claim-text:
1. A method to manufacture an electroluminescent display device, comprising:
forming a first electrode above a substrate;
forming a function layer including a luminescent layer on the first electrode;
sputtering a metallic material on the function layer in an atmosphere of an oxygen-containing carrier gas, so as to form a transparent second electrode made of a metal oxide on the function layer,
the partial pressure of oxygen in the carrier gas being increased with increased deposition of the metal oxide deposited on the function layer during the sputtering; and
controlling the partial pressure of oxygen in the carrier gas to be substantially zero during a predetermined time immediately from the start of the formation of the transparent second electrode while the amount of deposition is less than a predetermined film thickness during the sputtering.
